snippet.textDisplay:
Meaning of the song:

The female singer expresses the hurt she has felt when her lover said some mean things(khari khari, suna di khari re saiyaa) that they may not have meant from the heart but it was ugly and led to the break of their relationship.
When their loved ones say some things that hurt one deeply, this is what they may have felt.
It feels like, (andhi ruke na thami) a storm one started because of the ugly words has not stopped, (saanjh na din me dhali) the day has set and the morning does not seem to arise, it feels like night and darkness.

The hurt and pain, one feels because of undeserved ugly words is what has been highlighted here so beautifully.
Every note in the song I mean, awesomely touches that part of us that has grieved upon the death of a love once beautiful but now dead because of the ugly circumstances and words.

snippet.textDisplay: I fell in love with this song when watching 'Trishna' with  Freida Pinto over ten years ago, and it never gets old. The musical genius is other worldly. There is something deeply spiritual about how this song came to be and its execution. It's like the artists created their own cosmic bubble, connected to each other by the power of sound frequencies. AND the signers! I have no idea what they said, but I can feel the pain and longing the song conveys. I wish I could have witnessed this live. What a beautifully laid out set/stage/studio. ❤ Oh and  love how the sun come out at 4:16 ❤
